By Chimezie Godfrey The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria held a crucial meeting on strategic ways to build a sustainable aviation business in a post pandemic era. The key areas discussed in the meeting chaired by the MD/CE, Capt. Rabiu Yadudu include: Areas of operational efficiency, cost reduction, customer service, compliance to COVID-19 regulations, security, and synergy with other agencies, amongst others.   The meeting was attended by Directors in the Authority, General Managers and Regional Airport Managers.